reviewText: Great B film with wonderful character actors in supporting roles.  The usual vintage 40's fight scenes.  Pat O'Brien is terrific, projecting humanity while managing a bunch of untamed men in the oil field.  A fairly accurate peek into the world of oil wildcatting.  Rare opportunity to see Frances Farmer near the end of her brief film career.
Good but not one of Garfield's best.
Everytime I find some work of Frances Farmer I am full of joy. She was a complete actress and gorgeous as well.
